<div class="container mx-auto px-8 py-8 mt-8 pb-12">
  <!-- Back Button -->
  <%= link_to root_path, class: "btn btn-circle absolute left-4 top-4 sm:left-6 sm:top-6 z-50" do %>
    <%= lucide_icon 'arrow-left', class: 'size-6' %>
  <% end %>
  <!-- Page Header -->
  <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-8">
    <div class="size-12 rounded-lg bg-primary/10 flex items-center justify-center">
      <%= lucide_icon 'shield-check', class: 'size-6 text-primary' %>
    </div>
    <div>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold">Privacy Policy</h2>
      <p class="text-base-content/60">Last updated: July 7, 2025</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <!-- Main Content -->
  <div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-xl">
    <div class="card-body max-w-none">
      <h3 class="text-lg sm:text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mt-0 mb-1">1. Information We Collect</h3>
      <p class="mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">We collect information you provide directly to us when you:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc ml-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
        <li>Create an account</li>
        <li>Use our services</li>
        <li>Contact us for support</li>
        <li>Subscribe to our newsletters</li>
      </ul>
      <h3 class="text-lg sm:text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mt-4 mb-1">2. How We Use Your Information</h3>
      <p class="mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">We use the information we collect to:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc ml-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
        <li>Provide, maintain, and improve our services</li>
        <li>Process your transactions</li>
        <li>Send you technical notices and support messages</li>
        <li>Communicate with you about products, services, and events</li>
        <li>Protect against fraudulent or illegal activity</li>
      </ul>
      <h3 class="text-lg sm:text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mt-4 mb-1">3. Information Sharing</h3>
      <p class="mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">We do not sell or rent your personal information to third parties. We may share your information with:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc ml-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
        <li>Service providers who assist in our operations</li>
        <li>Professional advisers</li>
        <li>Law enforcement when required by law</li>
      </ul>
      <h3 class="text-lg sm:text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mt-4 mb-1">4. Data Security</h3>
      <p class="mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect your personal information against unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction.</p>
      <h3 class="text-lg sm:text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mt-4 mb-1">5. Your Rights</h3>
      <p class="mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">You have the right to:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc ml-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
        <li>Access your personal information</li>
        <li>Correct inaccurate data</li>
        <li>Request deletion of your data</li>
        <li>Object to our processing of your data</li>
        <li>Export your data</li>
      </ul>
      <h3 class="text-md sm:text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mt-2 mb-1">6. How to Delete Your Data</h4>
      <p class="mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
        If you wish to delete your data, you can do so at any time by unlinking your Facebook, Instagram, or Google account from your profile settings. Once you unlink your account(s), all associated user data will be deleted from our system. If you need assistance, please contact us at <%= mail_to "support@easystory.io", class: "text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400 underline" %>.
      </p>
      <h3 class="text-lg sm:text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mt-4 mb-1">7. Contact Us</h3>
      <p class="mb-1 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">If you have questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at <%= mail_to "support@easystory.io", class: "text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400 underline" %>.</p>
      <h3 class="text-lg sm:text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mt-4 mb-1">8. Cookies and Tracking Technologies</h3>
      <p class="mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">We may use cookies and similar tracking technologies to enhance your experience, analyze usage, and deliver relevant content. You can control the use of cookies through your browser settings, but disabling cookies may affect your ability to use certain features of our service.</p>
      <h3 class="text-lg sm:text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mt-4 mb-1">9. Data Retention</h3>
      <p class="mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">We retain your personal information only as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes described in this policy, comply with legal obligations, resolve disputes, and enforce our agreements. When your information is no longer needed, we will securely delete or anonymize it.</p>
      <h3 class="text-lg sm:text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mt-4 mb-1">10. International Data Transfers</h3>
      <p class="mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Your information may be transferred to and processed in countries other than your own, where data protection laws may differ. We take steps to ensure your data is protected and processed in accordance with this policy wherever it is handled.</p>
      <h3 class="text-lg sm:text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mt-4 mb-1">11. Children's Privacy</h3>
      <p class="mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Our service is not intended for children under 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If you believe a child has provided us with personal information, please contact us and we will take steps to delete such information.</p>
      <h3 class="text-lg sm:text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mt-4 mb-1">12. Changes to This Policy</h3>
      <p class="mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any material changes by posting the new policy on this page and updating the "Last updated" date. Your continued use of the service after changes are posted constitutes your acceptance of the revised policy.</p>
      <h3 class="text-lg sm:text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mt-4 mb-1">13. Region-Specific Rights</h3>
      <p class="mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Depending on your location, you may have additional rights under applicable data protection laws (such as the California Consumer Privacy Act or the EU General Data Protection Regulation). Please contact us if you wish to exercise any of these rights.</p>
      <h3 class="text-lg sm:text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mt-4 mb-1">14. Requests from Public Authorities</h3>
      <p class="mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
        We have established policies and processes for handling requests from public authorities for personal data or personal information of users:
        <ul class="list-disc ml-6 mt-2">
          <li><strong>Legality Review:</strong> All such requests are subject to a thorough review to ensure their legality and compliance with applicable laws.</li>
          <li><strong>Challenging Unlawful Requests:</strong> If a request is considered unlawful or overbroad, we reserve the right to challenge or refuse the request through appropriate legal channels.</li>
          <li><strong>Data Minimization:</strong> We disclose only the minimum amount of information necessary to comply with valid legal requests.</li>
          <li><strong>Documentation:</strong> We document all requests from public authorities, including our responses, the legal reasoning behind our actions, and the actors involved in the process.</li>
        </ul>
        These measures are in place to protect your privacy and ensure transparency in our handling of government or law enforcement requests.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
 